agent: New York State issues a Certificate of Title MV-999 for:
   most motor vehicles from model year 1973 or later;
    motor boats, 1987 or later model, measuring 14 feet or more user: What evidence should I give When requesting an original certificate of title? agent: When you request an original certificate of title, you must provide a signed proof of ownership, proof of sales tax payment, and proof of identity. user: and what vouchers should i send? agent: send proof of examples of your current address: a photocopy of your current record, driver's license, or utility bill. A new certificate of title that does not indicate the lien will be processed and mailed immediately.

agent: As proof of U.S. citizenship only certain documents are accepted. These include:
U.S. passport ;
Certificate of Naturalization N-550/N-570 ;
Certificate of Citizenship N-560/N-561 ;
Certificate of Report of Birth DS-1350 ;
Consular Report of Birth Abroad FS-240 , CRBA user: Do I need other documents? agent: We will also need to see your Employee identification card which must be current, not expired and show your name, identifying information such as date of birth or age and preferably a recent photograph user: And how do I prove my name change? agent: Proof of your legal name change must be shown and we accept an official Marriage document.
